 The Great Resignation and the war for talent point to the dire need for a change in the workforce. Add that with the pandemic woes, a 40-hour workweek is no longer sustainable. Fortunately, we’ve seen that there are better alternatives—countries like Iceland have paved the way by trialing a 4-day workweek (4DWW). The trial was a significant success, proving that this way of life is both possible and beneficial for the wellbeing and productivity of its citizens. Since then, few companies within the states have followed suit with the hopes of the same outcome. Read Full Story Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!